  {
    "objectID": "index.html",
    "href": "index.html",
    "title": "Sangīt Manjarī",
    "section": "",
    "text": "The Sangīt Manjarī was first published in 1907 under the patronage of Narendra Lall Khan, the king of Nārājole and Midnapore. This site presents a careful transliteration of the original Bengali notation into Roman script, preserving the swara-marks, octave indicators, and tāl structure of the source.\nCompositions are catalogued by rāga. Each page shows the lyrics followed by a notated table aligned to the relevant tāl cycle.\n\nTransliterated by Dr. Suparno Bhattacharyya. Published by SIMA — the Society for Indian Music and Arts."
  },
