    "title": "Rāg Āḍānā",
    "section": "Lyrics",
    "text": "Lyrics\n\nSthāyī\n\naba mori pāyelā bājanu solālana tihāre darasa hama kaise āu\n\nAntarā\n\njāgata hai mori nanadī jeṭhaniyāāvana ke samaya na pāu\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nNoteReading the notation\n\n\n\n\n\nTintāl is a 16-beat cycle divided as 4 + 4 + 4 + 4 (vibhāgs marked X, 2, O, 3). Each row below shows one complete cycle: the sixteen columns correspond to beats 1–16, with sam X at beat 1, 2 at beat 5, O (khālī) at beat 9, and 3 at beat 13.\nThe sargam row gives the notes; the bold text row below it gives the lyrics syllables. A dash - indicates a held note or empty beat. Brackets \\(\\lb{\\cdot}\\) denote meend (glide) or grouped notes; superscripts \\(\\sps{\\cdot}\\) indicate the starting grace note of a glide; \\(\\tr{X}\\) denotes a note in the upper octave (tār saptak); \\(\\mn{X}\\) denotes a note in the lower octave (mandra saptak)."
  },
