    "title": "Rāg Bāhār",
    "section": "Lyrics",
    "text": "Lyrics\n\nSthāyī\n\nāye ritu pati vasanta rāja,sakala dala sājana kara bolekoyeliyā rava sunata, śravaṅa kuhu ravamomana dara pāve\n\nAntarā\n\npraphullita saba vana ghanacampā bakula belari sabaati sugandha bahata pavanamanda manda ali kulavyākula bhaye\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nNoteReading the notation\n\n\n\n\n\nSuraphāktāl is a 10-beat cycle. In this notation, it is divided as 4 + 2 + 4 (vibhāgs marked X, 2, 3). Each row below shows one complete cycle: the ten columns correspond to beats 1–10, with sam X at beat 1, 2 at beat 5, and 3 at beat 7.\nThe sargam row gives the notes; the bold text row below it gives the lyrics syllables. A dash - indicates a held note or empty beat. Brackets \\(\\lb{\\cdot}\\) denote meend (glide) or grouped notes; superscripts \\(\\sps{\\cdot}\\) indicate the starting grace note of a glide; \\(\\tr{X}\\) denotes a note in the upper octave (tār saptak); \\(\\mn{X}\\) denotes a note in the lower octave (mandra saptak)."
  },
